# Local secrets — NEVER commit.
#
# Note: the *token* and *secret* globs below are intentionally broad. They
# will silently exclude ANY new file whose name contains "token" or
# "secret" — including files you might want to commit. Two safe escape
# hatches:
#   1. Streamlit Cloud — paste the contents of .streamlit/secrets.toml.example
#      into Settings → Secrets in the Streamlit Cloud UI. Streamlit holds them
#      in its own encrypted store and surfaces them to the app as
#      st.secrets[...] AND os.environ[...].
#   2. Local — keep your real values in .env (already excluded).
# If you NEED to track a file whose name matches these globs, add an
# explicit `!` exception below them (see secrets.toml.example for the
# pattern).
.env
.env.*
env (1)
github token
github_token
github-token
*.pem
*.key
*token*
*secret*
scripts/git token*

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.venv/
venv/
ENV/

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Streamlit cache / runtime
.streamlit/secrets.toml
.streamlit/cache/
# Allow the secrets template (which has only placeholder values) to
# be committed — overrides the broader ``*secret*`` rule above.
!.streamlit/secrets.toml.example

# Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb_checkpoints

# Generated reports / scratch files we don't version
*.docx
reports/
_tmp_*.py
_scratch/

# NOTE: data/ is INTENTIONALLY tracked in git. The GitHub Actions
# workflows commit daily updates back to the repo so `git pull` on
# your laptop is enough to get the latest prices, predictions,
# scored news, and FIPI flows. Do not add `data/` here.
#
# Per-user UI state (onboarding flag, dismissed tips, etc.).
# Each user has their own copy — should NOT be in git.
data/.ui_state.json
# Helper file used by commit scripts; never commit it.
_commit_msg.txt
# Cached raw PSX PDFs — typically 2-3 MB each, re-downloadable from PSX
# any time. We commit the structured `data/results/reports.parquet`
# (the LLM-extracted outlook + plans + risks) but NOT the source PDFs.
data/results/raw/
# Cached raw AHL Mutual Funds Equity Holdings + Market Performance
# PDFs (~600 KB each, re-downloadable from AHL Research). The
# structured outputs in `data/flows/*.parquet` are committed.
data/raw/
